snippet: According to preliminary entrance poll results, nearly six in ten voters consider themselves evangelical or born-again Christians.
abstract: According to preliminary entrance poll results, nearly six in ten voters consider themselves evangelical or born-again Christians.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES -- It looks like a similar proportion of evangelical voters is turning out for the caucuses this year, as compared to the four years ago.

headline.main: Entrance Polls Show High Evangelical Turnout
